Yes, this is due to the smaller sigma estimate of f2. In fact, the ratio of the squared sigma estimates of the two models, namely

sigma(f1)^2 / sigma(f2)^2

is identical to the ratio of the squared SEs of the two contrasts, namely

vcov(con1) / vcov(con2)

Best,
Wolfgang

